::Q1:: What is the primary purpose of Logistic Regression? {
    ~Solving regression problems
    =Solving classification problems
    ~Feature scaling
    ~Data visualization
}

::Q2:: Which of the following is an example of a classification problem? {
    ~Predicting house prices
    ~Predicting weather temperature
    =Identifying spam emails
    ~Predicting stock prices
}

::Q3:: What type of predicted value does Logistic Regression produce? {
    ~Continuous
    =Categorical
    ~Both continuous and categorical
    ~Neither continuous nor categorical
}

::Q4:: What is the key difference between Binary and Multivariate Logistic Regression? {
    ~Number of input features
    =Number of output classes
    ~Type of data used
    ~Algorithm used
}

::Q5:: In the context of Logistic Regression, what does the sigmoid function produce? {
    ~A linear output
    ~A categorical output
    =A probability score
    ~A binary output
}

::Q6:: Why is linear regression often unsuitable for classification problems directly? {
    ~It produces categorical outputs
    ~It's computationally expensive
    =Its output range is unbounded
    ~It requires large datasets
}

::Q7:: What is the shape of the cost function for Logistic Regression that is suitable for optimization? {
    ~Non-convex
    ~Linear
    =Convex
    ~Parabolic
}

::Q8:: What optimization algorithm is commonly used to find the optimal parameters in Logistic Regression? {
    ~Linear Programming
    =Gradient Descent
    ~Newton's Method
    ~Simulated Annealing
}

::Q9:: What is a decision boundary in the context of Logistic Regression? {
    =A line separating different classes
    ~The cost function value
    ~The gradient of the cost function
    ~The input features
}

::Q10:: What kind of learning technique is Logistic Regression? {
    ~Unsupervised Learning
    ~Reinforcement Learning
    =Supervised Learning
    ~Semi-supervised Learning
}
